main event: A UFO was reported in Eatontown, New Jersey, observed via ground radar on February 11, 1957.
interesting points: The object was tracked by CPS-6B radar, indicating it was likely a slower moving object due to wind conditions., The observation lasted for approximately 2 minutes., Various documents suggested the object may have been a balloon or possibly an aircraft., Another sighting from June 24, 1957, described a bright red object that appeared vapor-like., Observations noted the weather conditions were clear during the sightings.
witness description: civil service employee, U.S. Signal Corps
